<p style="text-align: justify;">Salman Khanâ€™s Tiger Zinda Hai has become Salmanâ€™s highest grossing film of all time that has been running strong at the box office. With each passing day, it has been continuing its roaring business. Salmanâ€™s previous highest grossing film was Bajrangi Bhaijaan that collected 320.34 crores. But Ali Abbas Tiger Zinda has entered its fourth week and collected 329.09 crores by adding 1 crore on its 4th Wednesday. As there is no big release until January 25, Tiger Zinda Hai has a chance to earn more at its usual pace. In next few days, it can cross 330 crores and eye on another milestone of 340 crores.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">Tiger Zinda Hai was released on December 22 and still ruling the box office despite many new releases.</p>
